Text.string: Come on, Vault Hunter. We got work to do.
Thanks for comin' all this way. Bet it was a schlep!
No matter how old I get, I still just love blowin' stuff up. And fire! Fire's great.
I can tell you've got hero written all over ya face! It's the dried blood, probably.
After this is over, I'd love to see your ship! Can't wait!
How many Sirens you got on that ship, anyway?
How's Pandora? Still... Pandora?
You smell like Eden-6! If you go back there, you tell the jabbers I said, “ook-ook!”
How's Promethea these days? Still got a ratch problem? Man, I could go for a ratchwich about now!
Don't you got something to do?
Look, I'd love to chat, but we got a universe to save!
I gotta make this right. For Leda.
Tyreen always was the strong one. Not just her powers—strong-willed, too! Never listened to me, unless I was telling her stories.
Troy, he was always sick. Those first days, I thought he'd die.
There's still time, Vault Hunter. We got a galaxy to save!
I'd trade it all for one more day with Leda.
Those Eridians were smart. Leda, she had a ton of theories about the Vaults, but she never wrote 'em down. Said it was too dangerous.
Grouse and Sparrow have kept me goin' through the bad times. I owe 'em my life!
Long ago, the Eridians locked an interdimensional monstrosity called the Destroyer in Pandora. They were strong, those aliens, but not strong enough kill it. And that's why we're in this mess!
A story can be a dangerous thing in the wrong hands.
I was a first-rate explorer but a third-rate pops. This is on me.
You're back!
There you are—we got a universe to save!
Doin' the best I can, Leda. I swear.
I miss ya, baby.
[humming] Digby Vermouth. Classic!
Where'd I put my Eridium? Know I hid it somewhere...
Well, Typhon. How you gonna get yourself outta this one?
Heya, Vault Hunter!
How's it goin'?
You doing all right, Vault Hunter?
Hi!
Hey!
Good day, Vault Hunter.
Not a bad day, eh, Vault Hunter?
Night's not so bad, eh, Vault Hunter?
You having a good night, Vault Hunter?
You still out there? We got a buttload of important stuff to do!
Get off your keister and help me save the universe!
No time to rest! We got important business, you and I.
You still alive, Vault Hunter?
You got somethin' important to do, right?
You take care of yourself, bub!
Okay. See ya later!
Where you goin'? Galaxy ain't gonna save itself, ya know!
Goodbye!
Guess I'm on my own now.
Later, VH!
Come back soon!
I'll see ya soon, Vault Hunter!
Buh-bye for now!
So long!
